Quick Review

  • Decision Trees. Used for Classification and Regression problems
  • Splits on metrics like entropy or information gain
  • Many implementations… we use sklearn.tree in this course

So When Should I Use Trees?

  • Patterns are often not linear. Trees can help you here

    • Logistic reg accuracy: 0.649
    • Tree accuracy 0.742

  • Tree Models are much easier to explain

    • as long as they're shallow
    • as long as there aren't too many features

It Doesn't Stop Here!

  • Trees are the foundation to a class of models, including

    • Random Forests, Fast & Frugal Trees, Conditional Inference Trees

  • Comparing Models is a cornerstone of Data Science!

    • “Best” model isn't always straightforward
    • Context matters, time & budget matter
